{"id": 232008154, "title": "Smethwick police charge two men after finding 1,000 cannabis plants at industrial site", "text": "Two men have been charged by West Midlands Police after 1,000 cannabis plants were discovered at an industrial unit in the Black Country. The plants were found at a site in Woodburn Road, Smethwick, after a warrant was executed on Friday, June 7. The force has charged two men with producing cannabis. The men, aged 32 and 36, of no fixed address, have been remanded to appear at Wolverhampton Magistrates Court tomorrow morning, June 10. A spokesperson for West Midlands Police said: \"We have charged two men after a cannabis farm was discovered by officers at a unit in Sandwell. We executed a warrant at an industrial unit on Woodburn Road, Smethwick on Friday morning. READ MORE: 'Courageous' West Midlands firefighter dies after cancer fight Get breaking news on BirminghamLive WhatsApp, click the link to join \"Once inside a cannabis grow of around 1,000 plants was discovered. Two men, aged 32 and 36, both of no fixed abode, have been charged with producing cannabis. \"They have been remanded in custody to appear at Wolverhampton Magistrates' Court tomorrow morning.\"", "summary": "The plants were discovered after a warrant was issued at an address in Woodburn Road, Smethwick, on June 10", "url": "https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/black-country/smethwick-police-charge-two-men-29321981", "image": "https://i2-prod.birminghammail.co.uk/incoming/article27260060.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/3_Wolverhampton-Magistrates-Court-in-North-Street.png", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 14:32:36", "author": "Jamie Brassington", "authors": ["Jamie Brassington"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.278}